Key Match Events: Yoshinobu Yamamoto struck out eight batters in a dazzling four-inning, one-run return from the injured list.
The Dodgers lost 6-3 to the Chicago Cubs at Dodger Stadium.
Numerous defensive miscues, including three errors in a decisive five-run eighth inning, contributed to each of the Cubs' tallies in their series-clinching win.
Tommy Edman hit two early home runs, his first of the season.
Max Muncy went deep in the fifth inning.
Post-Match Reflections: Manager Dave Roberts expressed frustration with the team's porous fielding, calling it 'very uncharacteristic.'
Austin Barnes took accountability for his errant throw, stating 'It was horrible. This one's on me.'
Max Muncy and Miguel Rojas had differing views on a defensive error, with Muncy expecting Rojas to cut off the play and Roberts explaining Rojas was trying to deke the runner.
